  19 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild:
  Removed polybori from Sage, but added cython to the list of blockers

  18 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild, +sage-4.2.1.ebuild.new:
  Fixed ECLDIR variable - now Sage should work with any version of
  ecls+maxima

  10 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild, +files/sage-4.2.1-amd64-hack.patch:
  Removed unsetting of ABI and moved unsets of C(XX)FLAGS to Sage's
  spkg-install file

  04 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild:
  Removed fortran stuff: lapack, blas

  01 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild, files/sage-4.2.1-singular-path-fix.patch:
  Added more documentation to the sed script which cleans Sage's makefile
  targets. Also adjust more singular paths. Singular will be built from
  Sage nevertheless, because libsingular has major differences to
  upstream

  01 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  -files/pari-2.3.3.p0-fix-ldconfig.patch, -sage-4.2.ebuild,
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild, -files/ecm-6.2.1.p0-fix-typo.patch,
  -files/deps-no-examples.patch, -files/eclib-fix-paths.patch,
  -files/g2red-pari-include-fix.patch, -files/install-no-doc.patch,
  -files/lcalc-fix-paths.patch, -files/linbox-fix-configure.patch,
  -files/sage-fix-paths.patch, -files/use-atlas-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-blas-from-portage.patch, -files/use-boehmgc-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-bzip2-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-cliquer-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-eclib-from-portage.patch, -files/use-ecm-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-freetype-from-portage.patch, -files/use-gap-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-gd-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-genus2reduction-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-givaro-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-gnutls-from-portage.patch, -files/use-gsl-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-iml-from-portage.patch, -files/use-lapack-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-lcalc-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-libfplll-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-libpng-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-linbox-from-portage.patch, -files/use-m4ri-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-maxima-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-mercurial-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-mpfi-from-portage.patch, -files/use-mpfr-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-mpir-from-portage.patch, -files/use-ntl-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-pari-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-readline-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-scons-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-singular-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-sqlite-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-tachyon-from-portage.patch, -files/use-zlib-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-znpoly-from-portage.patch:
  Removed support for sage-4.2 - update to sage-4.2.1! Also rewritten the
  code which cleans sage's makefile targets, now there are no patches
  needed. Everything will be done with sed.

  29 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild, +files/use-gap-from-portage.patch:
  Removed GAP

  28 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild, +files/sage-4.2.1-fix-rpy2.patch,
  +files/sage-4.2.1-singular-path-fix.patch,
  +files/sage-4.2.1-use-R-from-portage.patch,
  +files/use-m4ri-from-portage.patch,
  +files/use-singular-from-portage.patch:
  Removed R and m4ri from sage, added experimental singular patches -
  they will need more testing

  23 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild, +files/use-eclib-from-portage.patch,
  +files/use-genus2reduction-from-portage.patch,
  +files/use-lcalc-from-portage.patch:
  Replaced packages from sage : eclib, lcalc, genus2reduction

*sage-4.2.1 (22 Nov 2009)

  22 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild, +sage-4.2.1.ebuild:
  Added new sage-4.2.1. Compiles fine on x86, not yet tested

  19 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Removed sage packages: mpir, libfplll, tachyon, ecm. Not yet tested.

  18 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild, metadata.xml:
  Adjusted pari paths: GPHELP and GPDOCDIR. Also unset compilation flags
  on amd64 for testing

  17 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de> ChangeLog:
  Changed ebuild to not use system fortran compiler if USE=sage-minimal
  and also to not remove documentation and examples. Disabled parallel
  make.

  16 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Successfully removed maxima and introduced a patch for pari-data which
  fixes at least one test. Also added some notes about further proceeding.

  12 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Removed disable-* USE flags and added new USE-flag: sage-minimal which
  uses only a minimal subset of packages from portage

  11 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Added use-flags disable-mpfr and disable-pari which should help finding
  bugs on amd64

  10 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Removed dependency on maxima as this package is used from sage, added
  some comments about what should be done in future and patched two files
  to correctly make a link sage_pari->(/usr/bin/)gp

  09 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Removed usage of R from portage because of test failures. Force sage to
  use Fortran compiler already installed and added some comments on maxima
  and python. Thanks to Francois Bissey for providing me this information!

  08 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Removed mpfi, givaro, iml, zn_poly and linbox from sage's dependencies and
  replaced by DEPENDs. Introduces no additional test failures.

  07 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Removed freetype and gd from sage's dependencies and replaced by DEPENDs.
  This breaks none of the tests

  05 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Updated USE-flags, removed unneeded dependencies, temporarily falling
  back to sage maxima because sage could not start maxima from portage

  04 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  ChangeLog:
  Initial import - removed the following packages: atlas bzip2 gnutls gsl
  libpng maxima mercurial mpfr ntl pari R readline scons sqlite zlib

